[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

00:41:48.397 --> 00:41:50.480
DR. TEMPLE GRANDIN: And I
didn't do much studying,

00:41:50.480 --> 00:41:52.063
but I was in a special
boarding school

00:41:52.063 --> 00:41:54.650
for gifted kids with a
lot of emotional problems.

00:41:54.650 --> 00:41:57.150
And instead of studying,
I was remodeling

00:41:57.150 --> 00:41:58.599
our [INAUDIBLE] house.

00:41:58.599 --> 00:42:00.390
But the headmaster let
me do that because I

00:42:00.390 --> 00:42:02.790
was learning work skills.

00:42:02.790 --> 00:42:06.080
And a lot of these kids are
not learning work skills.

00:42:06.080 --> 00:42:08.680
I cleaned a lot of horse
stalls too when I was 15.

00:42:08.680 --> 00:42:10.090
Lots and lots of them.

00:42:10.090 --> 00:42:12.100
And I was responsible
for the horse barn

00:42:12.100 --> 00:42:14.360
and making sure I always
closed the feed box.

00:42:14.360 --> 00:42:17.160
Gotta always close the
grain box because a horse

00:42:17.160 --> 00:42:19.490
dies if eats out
of the grain box.

00:42:19.490 --> 00:42:21.610
You've got to close it.

00:42:21.610 --> 00:42:25.049
I think we need to limit
screen time with little kids.

00:42:25.049 --> 00:42:26.840
The thing that I'm
finding with electronics

00:42:26.840 --> 00:42:28.970
and with little kids
is yeah, little kids

00:42:28.970 --> 00:42:30.580
want to play with electronics.

00:42:30.580 --> 00:42:32.290
But we need to get
that teacher in there

00:42:32.290 --> 00:42:33.700
and get them taking turns.

00:42:33.700 --> 00:42:37.420
These kids have got to
learn how to take turns.

00:42:37.420 --> 00:42:39.900
Well, I think we need to
start making connections,

00:42:39.900 --> 00:42:42.460
physical connections
between the virtual world

00:42:42.460 --> 00:42:43.600
and the real world.

00:42:43.600 --> 00:42:47.410
And one really enterprising mom,
she went to the lumber yard,

00:42:47.410 --> 00:42:49.430
got some two by fours
cut up, and then she

00:42:49.430 --> 00:42:51.260
brought them all
home to the driveway

00:42:51.260 --> 00:42:53.590
and had the kids
paint them to make

00:42:53.590 --> 00:42:55.650
Minecraft blocks
in the driveway.

00:42:55.650 --> 00:42:59.520
In other words, linking the
online world to the real world.

00:42:59.520 --> 00:43:02.600
Then her little autistic kid
had lots of friends coming over

00:43:02.600 --> 00:43:06.020
to play with the
Minecraft blocks.

00:43:06.020 --> 00:43:07.480
Activities with animals.

00:43:07.480 --> 00:43:10.160
Get kids involved in activities
they can do with other kids.

00:43:10.160 --> 00:43:15.700
4H, FFA, robotics clubs,
maker bot, 3D printing clubs.

00:43:15.700 --> 00:43:18.650
Get them involved
in these things.

00:43:18.650 --> 00:43:20.890
My ability in art was
always encouraged.

00:43:20.890 --> 00:43:22.930
We need to be working
on building up

00:43:22.930 --> 00:43:25.930
the area of strength.

00:43:25.930 --> 00:43:29.740
The kid's good at math, let
him do more advanced classes.

00:43:29.740 --> 00:43:32.190
Use fixations to motivate.

00:43:32.190 --> 00:43:33.650
Great online sources.

00:43:33.650 --> 00:43:36.500
Now I was reading
that on Audacity

00:43:36.500 --> 00:43:38.950
or some of these things
like this, that only 4%

00:43:38.950 --> 00:43:41.700
